            <h2>WHAT CAN MARGIN SAVER GRAIN DO?</h2>
            <div class="features">
                <div class="feature">
                    <h3>Optimize Shipment Selections</h3>
                    <p>Offers a comprehensive view of the most profitable potential shipping origins, automatic quality analyzation, and origination tools.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="feature">
                    <h3>Inventory Awareness and Accountability Tools</h3>
                    <p>Analyzes location inventories to create the most efficient lots or blends, matching commodity grades to account contracts or standard discounts, and suggests top shipping locations to maximize margins. Considering left over inventory implications and protecting future margins.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="feature">
                    <h3>Carbon Inventory Tracking and Shrink Accumulator</h3>
                    <p>Integrates with ERP, Scale, or third-party carbon information to build a perspective of in-house grain with associated carbon indicators. Shrink tracking tool gives the user the ability to generate more accurate inventory shrink data and allows for more timely and profitable adjustments.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <h3>AUTOMATIC GENERATION OF:</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Best Quality and Freight Outbound Margin Situation for multiple sites or a single site's bins</li>
                <li>Mix and Blend site performance metrics</li>
                <li>At Risk Grain Positions: Scale and Weather based</li>
                <li>Most Profitable Farmer Client List</li>
                <li>Total Shrink Losses per Commodity</li>
                <li>All sites Carbon Inventory</li>
                <li>Nearby Posted Bid Scraper and Mapping</li>
